7. house rules  
Should it be possible to drop Chests/Treasures/etc?  
- > NO. Once a chest, treasure, wyrdstone shard, or any other objective Was picked up, it cannot be dropped voluntarily. The goal is to prevent abuse from fst chars carriying boxes and dropping them and to prevent manipulating the movement of NPCs.

9. Second Table

48x48 inch table
Zweit Tische der größe 48x48? => nein einen 48x72 Tisch für die multiplayer spiele (3+ Spieler). Den haben wir ja schon. Nun brauchen wir noch einen für die 2 Spieler Szenarios 

10. Matchmaking

Viertens Wird ersetzt durch:
The Player with the lowest Campaign Points (CP) chooses an opponent. Then he rolls a D6:
1-2: choose a scenario | 3-5: randomize the scenario by rolling a D20/10 | 6: the opponent chooses the scenario
If a multiplayer scenario is chosen, the Player selecting the scenario also selects the additional Player 
If the scenario requires to choose a defender/attacker, the Player Who chose the scenario assigns roles. 

11. NPC Movement 

All Npcs move/charge according to the rules:
1 IF possible, the npc Charges (charge distance = March distance) 
2 IF no enemy is in charge distance, the NPC either makes a march move towards its objective or moves at random (2D6? Or march?)
3 IF any enemy model has attacked the npc, or Contests an objective which the npc is guarding, this Model has the highest priority for the npc
4 IF two or more enemy models are tied for priority, the npc randomizes between them. 

12. Auswahl der Wrabands  
 - Wollen wir irgendwelche Warbands aus dem Grundbuch verbieten? (Forest-Walker und Skyre wären z.B. Kandidaten, andere aber auch)  
 - Nach möglichkeit sollte es halbwegs ausgewogen sein zwischen guten und bösen Warbands (hat aber keine so hohe Prio)  
 - Vielleicht macht es Sinn jeweils (mindestens) eine Warband mit der Objective Scion of Chaos (der böse Angreifer in der Kampagne) und Celestial Protectorate (der gute Verteidiger) zu haben  
